# DiagnoVision Project Rules

## Database Schema

### Firebase Tables

**user** ( id, email, password, role )

**patient** ( user_id, name, age, gender, doctorId, contactNo )

**doctor** ( user_id, name, qualification, licenseNo )

**messages** ( msg_id, patientId, doctorId, msg, sent_by_patient )

**notifications** ( user_id, notification )

**glucoma_result** ( patientId, result_msg, imageId, doctor_feedback, date )

**dr_result** ( patientId, result_msg, imageId, doctor_feedback, date )

**appointments** ( id, patientID, doctorID, Date, status )

### Supabase Tables

**images** ( imageId, Image_url, heatmap_url, overlay_url, grad_cam_url )

### Notes
- Supabase stores images and will store references in image table
- Both glucoma_result and dr_result reference images via imageId
- Firebase handles user authentication and data storage
- Supabase handles image storage and retrieval

## Tech Stack

### Frontend
- **React.js** - UI framework (using Vite as build tool)
- **React Router** - Client-side routing
- **Tailwind CSS** - Styling framework
- **Firebase** - Authentication and user data storage
- **Supabase** - Image storage and retrieval

### Backend/ML
- **FastAPI** - Backend API for ML model inference
- **ML Models** - Glaucoma and Diabetic Retinopathy detection
- **GradCAM** - Model explainability/visualization

### Key Features
- Image upload and storage in Supabase
- ML model inference via FastAPI
- GradCAM heatmap generation for explainability
- Real-time results stored in Firebase
- Role-based access (Patient/Doctor)

## Project Setup
- Installation scripts provided: `install.bat` (Windows) and `install.sh` (Linux/Mac)
- Run `npm install` or use the install scripts to set up dependencies
- Run `npm run dev` to start the development server
- Make sure to add a file so whenever someone clones from GitHub they can easily just run that file and download all the dependencies
- Make sure to do everything such that when we push to GitHub and someone clones it, then they should be easily able to download the dependencies and run the project

